Image SpecificationsCard Images (images/cards/)

Create a [trex] real life image 
Size: 600 × 400px (landscape)
File Type: JPG
File size: Keep under 500KB for fast loading
What it shows: The full dinosaur body, ideally with some background/habitat. Think "hero shot" — the whole animal visible.
Scene Images (images/scenes/)

Size: 900 × 600px (landscape works best, portrait is fine too)
Format: JPG
File size: Keep under 500KB
What it shows: Can be more dramatic/close-up. This is the big feature image when you click into a dinosaur. Environment/mood matters here.
🖼️ Good Free Sources for ImagesWikimedia Commons (free, high quality scientific art)

Go to commons.wikimedia.org
Search: "Tyrannosaurus life restoration", "Triceratops reconstruction", etc.
Filter by image, download the largest version, resize to spec
Other options:

Midjourney / DALL-E / Adobe Firefly — prompt: "photorealistic Tyrannosaurus Rex, Cretaceous swamp, National Geographic wildlife photography, wide shot showing full body, dramatic lighting"
Prehistoric Planet press images (Google search)
Natural History Museum image library
📁 How to Add to GitHub


Go to your repo at github.com/jeffbtruitt-gif/Dino-Explorer
Click into images/cards/
Click Add file → Upload files
Drop in all 6 card images (named exactly as shown below)
Click Commit changes

Go back, click into images/scenes/
Repeat — upload all 6 scene images
Commit
File names must match exactly (lowercase, no spaces):
images/cards/trex.jpg
images/cards/triceratops.jpg
images/cards/brachiosaurus.jpg
images/cards/velociraptor.jpg
images/cards/stegosaurus.jpg
